Netflix is due to release a programme on the hostage drama involving the Bloemfontein teacher. JOHANNESBURG - American television network Netflix is due to release a programme on Friday on the hostage drama involving Bloemfontein teacher, Pierre Korkie.Tuesday marks the second anniversary of Korkie's death. He was taken hostage by al-Qaeda militants in Yemen and was killed during a rescue attempt. The Gift of the Givers led the negotiations to secure his release. Founder Imtiaaz Sooliman says: Today (6 December) is a very sad day for many of us in South Africa, especially for the Korkie family. It s the day that Pierre Korkie was supposed to get his freedom, however he died in an American raid. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)